  <h1>
   view_get_visible
  </h1>
  This function can be used to check the visibility of the given view port. The function will return
  <span>
   true
  </span>
  if it is visible and
  <span>
   false
  </span>
  if it is not.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">view_get_visible(view_port)
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      view_port
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The view port to target (0 - 7)
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Boolean
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">if !view_get_visible(0)
{
    view_set_visible(0, true);
}
</code></pre>
  The above code will check to see if the view port[0] is visible and if it is not it is set to visible.
 </body>
